TITLE: Defining DropdownItemSelectedIconProps Type in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet defines the DropdownItemSelectedIconProps type and the selectedIcon type for the DropdownItem component. It specifies the structure for custom icons used when an item is selected.
SOURCE: https://github.com/heroui-inc/heroui/blob/canary/apps/docs/content/docs/components/dropdown.mdx#2025-04-20_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
export type DropdownItemSelectedIconProps = {
  /**
   * The current icon, usually an checkmark icon.
   */
  icon?: ReactNode;
  /**
   * The current selected status.
   */
  isSelected?: boolean;
  /**
   * The current disabled status.
   * @default false
   */
  isDisabled?: boolean;
};

type selectedIcon?: ReactNode | ((props: DropdownItemSelectedIconProps) => ReactNode) | null;
```

